docs.abstract: The Treasury Department expressed concern about China’s weakening currency but declined, again, to officially call it a manipulator.
docs.snippet: The Treasury Department expressed concern about China’s weakening currency but declined, again, to officially call it a manipulator.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is eagerly embracing a trade war with China, but on Wednesday, it opted once again not to label that nation a currency manipulator despite President Trump’s repeated complaint that Beijing is weakening the renminbi.

headline.main: Treasury Opts Against Labeling China a Currency Manipulator
headline.print_headline: U.S. Opts Not to Call China A Currency Manipulator

docs.lead_paragraph: Allyn Ann McLerie, who drew attention on Broadway when she was 21 in “Where’s Charley?,” then became a familiar screen presence through numerous movie and television roles, died on May 21 in North Bend, Wash. She was 91.

docs.abstract: The president’s partner in Dubai has tapped a company controlled by the government in Beijing to help build a project featuring an 18-hole course designed by Tiger Woods.
docs.snippet: The president’s partner in Dubai has tapped a company controlled by the government in Beijing to help build a project featuring an 18-hole course designed by Tiger Woods.
docs.lead_paragraph: A new Trump-affiliated real-estate project in Dubai will feature an 18-hole golf course designed by Tiger Woods, extensive greenery and hundreds of luxury villas. A company controlled by Beijing will help make it a reality.

headline.main: Complex With New Trump Golf Club Will Get Chinese Help

docs.abstract: Apps help guide the blind through airports. Smartphones help the deaf communicate. But tech’s advantages often stop at the door of the plane, train or bus.
docs.snippet: Apps help guide the blind through airports. Smartphones help the deaf communicate. But tech’s advantages often stop at the door of the plane, train or bus.
docs.lead_paragraph: Technology is fast changing how people with disabilities get to and then navigate airports and train and bus stations. But technology can go only so far: Its advantages usually stop at the door of the plane, train or bus.

headline.main: For Disabled Travelers, Technology Helps Smooth the Way. But Not All of It.
headline.print_headline: Tech Makes Life Easier for Disabled Travelers, Until They Board
